SapuraCrest Petroleum Bhd. (SCRES)  and
 Kencana Petroleum Bhd. (KEPB)  said today they are accepting the 11.9
billion ringgit ($3.9 billion) merger offer to create Malaysiaâ€™s
second-largest listed oilfield services company.  Integral Key Sdn., a special purpose vehicle, bid 4.60
ringgit per share in stock and cash for SapuraCrest and the
equivalent of 3 ringgit per share for Kencana, the companies
said in separate Kuala Lumpur exchange filings. Their assets and
